1
00:00:06,041 --> 00:00:07,721
WOMAN: Can you hear me?

2
00:00:18,401 --> 00:00:19,601
MAN: Thief!

3
00:00:21,041 --> 00:00:22,721
- Let me back in!
- How did you get out there?

4
00:00:22,841 --> 00:00:24,961
- Seeing a friend.
- I'll chop your hand off!

5
00:00:25,081 --> 00:00:26,121
I say friend...
We're not that close.

6
00:00:26,241 --> 00:00:27,481
Please, let me back in.

7
00:00:27,601 --> 00:00:30,481
Please! Let me back in fast.

8
00:00:35,921 --> 00:00:38,121
You can't keep stealing
from merchants in the souk.

9
00:00:38,241 --> 00:00:40,041
They know where you're from.

10
00:00:40,161 --> 00:00:42,001
You tell me creating happiness

11
00:00:42,121 --> 00:00:44,601
is important
to my mental well being.

12
00:00:44,721 --> 00:00:46,361
A game like this
makes me happy.

13
00:00:46,481 --> 00:00:48,161
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

14
00:00:48,281 --> 00:00:51,001
Time to go back in your room.
It'll be dark soon.

15
00:00:51,121 --> 00:00:53,401
Have you taken precautions?
Have you told everyone?

16
00:00:53,521 --> 00:00:54,801
Tahira...

17
00:00:54,921 --> 00:00:56,801
We have to keep everyone safe.

18
00:00:56,921 --> 00:00:57,921
Nothing is going to happen,
Tahira.

19
00:00:58,041 --> 00:01:00,241
Of course it is.
I told you to tell them.

20
00:01:00,361 --> 00:01:03,201
I told the doctors,
I told all of you.

21
00:01:03,321 --> 00:01:04,841
They're real.

22
00:01:04,961 --> 00:01:07,361
I understand
they seem real to you.

23
00:01:08,961 --> 00:01:11,161
You need to rest.
Sleep will help.

24
00:01:11,281 --> 00:01:14,121
Sleep is when they'll come.

25
00:01:15,681 --> 00:01:17,601
I can feel them coming.

26
00:01:18,801 --> 00:01:20,721
They'll be here tonight.

27
00:01:21,801 --> 00:01:22,801
Rest well, Tahira.

28
00:01:25,561 --> 00:01:27,081
(SIGHS)

29
00:01:27,201 --> 00:01:29,121
(DISTANT BIRD CALLING)

30
00:01:38,801 --> 00:01:40,001
(FLAME CRACKLES)

31
00:01:41,121 --> 00:01:43,401
TAHIRA: Maryam. Maryam!

32
00:01:43,521 --> 00:01:45,481
MARYAM: Over here.

33
00:01:45,601 --> 00:01:47,321
I told you to lock the doors.

34
00:01:47,441 --> 00:01:50,401
- We don't do that.
- Get everyone out.

35
00:01:52,921 --> 00:01:54,081
(SNARLING)

36
00:01:54,201 --> 00:01:56,681
MARYAM: Oh, no.

37
00:01:56,801 --> 00:01:58,001
(GUTTURAL GROWL)

38
00:01:58,121 --> 00:01:59,801
TAHIRA: I tried to warn you.

39
00:01:59,921 --> 00:02:02,361
(MUFFLED GASP)

40
00:02:02,481 --> 00:02:04,361
Don't struggle.

41
00:02:05,681 --> 00:02:07,201
They like it more
when you struggle.

42
00:02:10,561 --> 00:02:12,361
(ROARS)

43
00:02:13,641 --> 00:02:15,961
- (CLATTERING)
- (GASPS)

44
00:02:16,081 --> 00:02:18,601
- (SCREAMING)
- (GROWLING AND CRUNCHING)

45
00:02:18,721 --> 00:02:21,441
(SCREAMING)

46
00:02:21,561 --> 00:02:23,361
(GROWLING)

47
00:02:23,481 --> 00:02:24,721
(THUDDING)

48
00:02:24,841 --> 00:02:25,841
(GASPS)

49
00:02:25,961 --> 00:02:28,441
(THUDDING)

50
00:02:34,161 --> 00:02:36,481
- Oh.
- (GROWLS)

51
00:03:12,481 --> 00:03:16,241
(TARDIS THRUMS)

52
00:03:19,841 --> 00:03:21,081
DOCTOR: Here we are -
Sheffield.

53
00:03:21,201 --> 00:03:22,281
YAZ: Is it the right day?

54
00:03:22,401 --> 00:03:23,641
- It's the right day.
- In the right year?

55
00:03:23,761 --> 00:03:25,001
The day you asked,
in the year that you asked,

56
00:03:25,121 --> 00:03:26,041
at the time that you asked.

57
00:03:26,161 --> 00:03:28,041
You are home.

58
00:03:29,841 --> 00:03:32,121
Everyone meet back here
tomorrow lunchtime?

59
00:03:32,241 --> 00:03:33,961
- Yeah, yeah.
- What are you going to do?

60
00:03:34,081 --> 00:03:35,961
Me? Oh, yeah.

61
00:03:36,081 --> 00:03:37,521
Very busy.

62
00:03:38,601 --> 00:03:40,281
Busy, busy. Maintenance.

63
00:03:40,401 --> 00:03:41,601
Correspondence.

64
00:03:41,721 --> 00:03:43,281
Correspondence
about maintenance.

65
00:03:43,401 --> 00:03:44,441
- (BEEPING)
- Oh!

66
00:03:45,521 --> 00:03:47,401
Oh. OK.

67
00:03:47,521 --> 00:03:50,321
Not the exact right time -
77 minutes out. Late.

68
00:03:50,441 --> 00:03:52,921
What?! (HUFFS)

69
00:03:53,041 --> 00:03:54,361
You sure you're going to be

70
00:03:54,481 --> 00:03:56,321
- all right on your own?
- Oh, you know.

71
00:03:56,441 --> 00:03:58,961
Finally a bit of peace
and quiet.

72
00:03:59,081 --> 00:04:00,481
(DOOR CLOSES)

73
00:04:01,641 --> 00:04:03,081
Hmm...

74
00:04:04,961 --> 00:04:06,281
I could always...

75
00:04:07,441 --> 00:04:09,361
Oh, nah.

76
00:04:10,721 --> 00:04:13,001
Maybe I'll just nip
straight to tomorrow lunchtime.

77
00:04:14,361 --> 00:04:18,321
(GROWLING)

78
00:04:18,441 --> 00:04:19,841
What was that?

79
00:04:28,481 --> 00:04:30,081
(BEEPING)

80
00:04:30,201 --> 00:04:32,001
Location for that noise.

81
00:04:32,121 --> 00:04:33,241
Aleppo?

82
00:04:34,721 --> 00:04:35,761
I've got time.

83
00:04:38,481 --> 00:04:39,841
(TARDIS THRUMS)

84
00:04:39,961 --> 00:04:42,361
Sorry, sorry.

85
00:04:42,481 --> 00:04:44,681
Am I late?
It is the right day, isn't it?

86
00:04:44,801 --> 00:04:46,601
Have you been waiting long?
Am I really late?

87
00:04:46,721 --> 00:04:49,561
Yes, yes, yes and yes.

88
00:04:49,681 --> 00:04:51,681
Mum and Dad left hours ago.

89
00:04:51,801 --> 00:04:53,721
Whitby for the night.

90
00:04:53,841 --> 00:04:55,321
Did you cook?

91
00:04:56,361 --> 00:04:57,641
Can you cook now?

92
00:05:00,081 --> 00:05:01,601
Hi, loser.

93
00:05:04,681 --> 00:05:05,801
Hey, no-mark.

94
00:05:07,481 --> 00:05:08,521
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

95
00:05:08,641 --> 00:05:12,201
(MULTIPLE BOLTS CLANK
AND UNLOCK)

96
00:05:15,921 --> 00:05:16,921
What are you doing here, man?

97
00:05:17,041 --> 00:05:18,681
I got your messages, didn't I?

98
00:05:18,801 --> 00:05:20,881
- It's been months.
- Yeah.

99
00:05:21,001 --> 00:05:22,441
Me phone's been playing up.

100
00:05:25,121 --> 00:05:27,161
- So, are you back?
- Yeah.

101
00:05:27,281 --> 00:05:28,561
Sort of.

102
00:05:28,681 --> 00:05:30,481
Not really. Just a few hours.

103
00:05:30,601 --> 00:05:32,681
I bought chips.
You going to let me in or what?

104
00:05:33,761 --> 00:05:35,241
It's not a good time.

105
00:05:37,441 --> 00:05:39,721
(JOKINGLY) I got chips, though!

106
00:05:39,841 --> 00:05:41,201
(LAUGHS)

107
00:05:53,241 --> 00:05:54,481
GRAHAM: Now, that, gentlemen,

108
00:05:54,601 --> 00:05:58,201
- is a full house.
- What?

109
00:05:58,321 --> 00:06:01,641
Well, I've been practising,
haven't I? On my travels, eh?

110
00:06:01,761 --> 00:06:03,281
I've got to say,
it's great to see you lads.

111
00:06:03,401 --> 00:06:04,561
It don't sound like
I've been missing much, though.

112
00:06:04,681 --> 00:06:06,081
(SCOFFS) Nothin' at all.

113
00:06:06,201 --> 00:06:07,681
I'd rather be on cruises
like you.

114
00:06:07,801 --> 00:06:09,801
Well, let me tell you, Gabe,
those boats, mate,

115
00:06:09,921 --> 00:06:11,761
they are lovely - very calm.

116
00:06:11,881 --> 00:06:13,601
And how's your health now,
Gray, you all right?

117
00:06:13,721 --> 00:06:15,201
Good, Freddie boy, thanks.
Very good.

118
00:06:15,321 --> 00:06:16,961
How are you coping...

119
00:06:17,961 --> 00:06:18,881
...without Grace?

120
00:06:19,001 --> 00:06:21,521
Well, I have to, don't I?
You know.

121
00:06:21,641 --> 00:06:23,561
Travelling helps, mate,
don't it?

122
00:06:23,681 --> 00:06:26,001
Stops me
getting stuck in the past.

123
00:06:26,121 --> 00:06:27,521
(TARDIS THRUMS)

124
00:06:35,481 --> 00:06:37,961
(SIGHS) Aleppo.

125
00:06:38,081 --> 00:06:40,121
1380. Welcome to Syria!

126
00:06:40,241 --> 00:06:41,521
Now...

127
00:06:41,641 --> 00:06:44,041
Oh. (SMACKS LIPS)

128
00:06:44,161 --> 00:06:45,401
They're not here, are they?

129
00:06:46,761 --> 00:06:48,001
"Bimaristan."

130
00:06:49,681 --> 00:06:51,081
It means sick place.

131
00:06:51,201 --> 00:06:52,321
This must be

132
00:06:52,441 --> 00:06:55,041
one of the oldest hospitals
in the world.

133
00:06:55,161 --> 00:06:57,041
Of course, Islamic physicians
were known

134
00:06:57,161 --> 00:06:58,201
for the enlightened way

135
00:06:58,321 --> 00:07:00,281
they treated people
with mental health problems.

136
00:07:03,041 --> 00:07:05,081
But what happened here?

137
00:07:05,201 --> 00:07:06,521
You guys go this way...

138
00:07:06,641 --> 00:07:07,841
Oh! Who am
I supposed to share

139
00:07:07,961 --> 00:07:09,321
all the interesting stuff
with?!

140
00:07:09,441 --> 00:07:10,441
TAHIRA: Is someone there?

141
00:07:12,001 --> 00:07:14,201
Friendly visitors. Visitor.

142
00:07:14,321 --> 00:07:15,841
Where are you?

143
00:07:15,961 --> 00:07:17,961
I'm coming to say hello.

144
00:07:19,041 --> 00:07:20,201
(SOBBING)

145
00:07:20,321 --> 00:07:21,601
I'm the Doctor.

146
00:07:23,361 --> 00:07:24,801
I'm here to help.

147
00:07:24,921 --> 00:07:28,681
(SOBBING CONTINUES)

148
00:07:28,801 --> 00:07:29,761
Stay away!

149
00:07:29,881 --> 00:07:32,001
It's all right.
You're safe, I promise.

150
00:07:32,121 --> 00:07:34,001
No, they took everyone.

151
00:07:34,121 --> 00:07:35,601
What happened here?

152
00:07:35,721 --> 00:07:38,201
- You have to get out!
- Why?

153
00:07:38,321 --> 00:07:40,881
Because there's one still here.

154
00:07:41,001 --> 00:07:44,121
(GROWLING)

155
00:07:47,121 --> 00:07:48,441
(ROARS)

156
00:07:50,241 --> 00:07:51,081
(GASPS)

157
00:07:54,081 --> 00:07:55,361
(GROWLS)

158
00:07:55,481 --> 00:07:57,521
What are you?

159
00:07:57,641 --> 00:07:58,561
Leave her alone!

160
00:07:58,681 --> 00:08:00,801
(ROARS)

161
00:08:00,921 --> 00:08:02,521
Stay here!

162
00:08:04,121 --> 00:08:05,601
Gone. That was fast.

163
00:08:05,721 --> 00:08:08,801
(SONIC WHIRS)

164
00:08:08,921 --> 00:08:10,561
(BEEPS)

165
00:08:10,681 --> 00:08:11,681
Nothing.

166
00:08:13,441 --> 00:08:14,721
Nothing at all.

167
00:08:17,161 --> 00:08:19,481
Right, lads, ready?
Here we go.

168
00:08:19,601 --> 00:08:22,521
Fastest dealer
in South Yorkshire.

169
00:08:22,641 --> 00:08:24,481
(WHOOSHING)

170
00:08:37,121 --> 00:08:38,401
Can you see?

171
00:08:40,481 --> 00:08:42,361
Can you see it?

172
00:08:44,601 --> 00:08:45,761
I'm trapped.

173
00:08:47,001 --> 00:08:48,601
This is what he did to me.

174
00:08:49,761 --> 00:08:51,601
Help me, Graham.

175
00:08:51,721 --> 00:08:52,761
He's close.

176
00:08:56,841 --> 00:08:58,201
I think you lost count.

177
00:08:58,321 --> 00:08:59,441
Huh?

178
00:09:01,081 --> 00:09:02,361
(FOOTBALL VIDEO GAME PLAYS)

179
00:09:03,561 --> 00:09:04,561
Goes past one...

180
00:09:05,841 --> 00:09:07,001
Goes past two...

181
00:09:08,321 --> 00:09:09,761
It's a screamer!

182
00:09:09,881 --> 00:09:12,441
Top bins! Final seconds...

183
00:09:12,561 --> 00:09:14,481
He's done it. He's a lege.

184
00:09:14,601 --> 00:09:16,201
Ryan Sinclair, FIFA legend.

185
00:09:16,321 --> 00:09:17,641
I've never lost it.

186
00:09:17,761 --> 00:09:19,161
Oh! I've still got it.

187
00:09:22,841 --> 00:09:24,161
I'll make tea.

188
00:09:33,721 --> 00:09:35,241
Your place
ls normally spotless.

189
00:09:35,361 --> 00:09:36,481
This ain't you.

190
00:09:36,601 --> 00:09:38,441
Mate, you ain't been around,
so don't tell me what I am.

191
00:09:38,561 --> 00:09:39,561
All right.

192
00:09:43,161 --> 00:09:45,401
Mate, sorry for not answering
your messages.

193
00:09:45,521 --> 00:09:47,401
(CAN CRUNCHES)

194
00:09:49,361 --> 00:09:51,321
But you ain't yourself.

195
00:09:53,081 --> 00:09:56,401
I'm just finding things
difficult at the moment.

196
00:09:56,521 --> 00:09:58,201
Have you spoke
to anyone about it?

197
00:09:58,321 --> 00:10:00,561
No, and I'm not going to.

198
00:10:00,681 --> 00:10:02,201
All right.

199
00:10:05,321 --> 00:10:06,681
There's something else.

200
00:10:08,321 --> 00:10:09,321
Promise you won't laugh at me.

201
00:10:09,441 --> 00:10:10,681
I can't promise that, can I?

202
00:10:12,081 --> 00:10:14,121
(SIGHS)

203
00:10:19,321 --> 00:10:20,601
Last few days...

204
00:10:22,041 --> 00:10:23,601
...I've been having nightmares.

205
00:10:24,681 --> 00:10:26,481
Dark, messed-up stuff.

206
00:10:28,001 --> 00:10:29,321
And there's this...

207
00:10:29,441 --> 00:10:30,561
...bloke in them.

208
00:10:31,641 --> 00:10:35,721
He keeps recurring,
like he's watching my dreams,

209
00:10:35,841 --> 00:10:37,281
waiting in the dark.

210
00:10:37,401 --> 00:10:38,841
Oh, that's creepy.

211
00:10:38,961 --> 00:10:40,081
That's not the mad bit.

212
00:10:41,721 --> 00:10:43,921
But the past few days...

213
00:10:45,321 --> 00:10:46,721
...I've seen him.

214
00:10:48,241 --> 00:10:50,841
At night. Outside the flat.
Across the hall.

215
00:10:53,561 --> 00:10:54,801
In my room.

216
00:10:54,921 --> 00:10:57,001
The guy that's in your dreams
is in your room?

217
00:10:57,121 --> 00:10:58,361
I knew you'd laugh.

218
00:10:58,481 --> 00:11:00,161
Look at me.

219
00:11:00,281 --> 00:11:01,641
I'm not laughing.

220
00:11:02,841 --> 00:11:04,841
Mate, I've seen
some weird things

221
00:11:04,961 --> 00:11:06,281
while I've been away.

222
00:11:06,401 --> 00:11:08,481
Things you wouldn't believe
are possible.

223
00:11:12,601 --> 00:11:14,241
Would you kip here tonight?

224
00:11:15,961 --> 00:11:17,161
So, can you say
where you've been,

225
00:11:17,281 --> 00:11:18,641
where they sent you?

226
00:11:18,761 --> 00:11:19,921
Madagascar.

227
00:11:20,041 --> 00:11:21,321
California. Hong Kong.

228
00:11:21,441 --> 00:11:23,321
- Gloucester.
- Oh!

229
00:11:23,441 --> 00:11:24,921
They had a thing in Gloucester.

230
00:11:25,041 --> 00:11:27,521
Dad was going on about it.
Something to do with Russians.

231
00:11:27,641 --> 00:11:29,841
It had nowt to do
with Russians.

232
00:11:32,041 --> 00:11:33,801
- How's the new job?
- Sacked.

233
00:11:34,881 --> 00:11:36,281
- Sonya.
- What?

234
00:11:36,401 --> 00:11:37,961
That's the third time!

235
00:11:38,081 --> 00:11:40,201
People are really annoying,
and they hate being told that.

236
00:11:40,321 --> 00:11:42,161
I'm just not cut out
for customer services.

237
00:11:42,281 --> 00:11:43,441
No kidding!

238
00:11:45,881 --> 00:11:47,281
Sonya...

239
00:11:50,841 --> 00:11:52,921
We can stop doing this.

240
00:11:53,041 --> 00:11:54,321
Stop marking it.

241
00:11:55,841 --> 00:11:57,321
I thought it was a good thing.

242
00:11:59,401 --> 00:12:00,561
Yeah.

243
00:12:00,681 --> 00:12:03,681
No, I just don't know whether
an anniversary dinner...

244
00:12:03,801 --> 00:12:04,961
I still think about it.

245
00:12:07,001 --> 00:12:08,801
Do you?

246
00:12:11,921 --> 00:12:13,881
I dream about it sometimes.

247
00:12:18,161 --> 00:12:19,281
Sofa movie after?

248
00:12:19,401 --> 00:12:22,321
What, so you can fall asleep
halfway through?

249
00:12:22,441 --> 00:12:23,921
I do not do that.

250
00:12:24,041 --> 00:12:28,001
(INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC ON TV)

251
00:12:29,561 --> 00:12:31,401
Idiot.

252
00:12:32,481 --> 00:12:33,721
(PHONE RINGS)

253
00:12:33,841 --> 00:12:35,161
SONYA: Hi.

254
00:12:35,281 --> 00:12:38,321
I-I didn't know who to call.
We need help.

255
00:13:06,001 --> 00:13:07,441
(GASPS)

256
00:13:07,561 --> 00:13:09,561
(LAUGHTER)

257
00:13:19,041 --> 00:13:20,281
Who are you?

258
00:13:20,401 --> 00:13:22,081
What are you doing here?

259
00:13:25,281 --> 00:13:26,761
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

260
00:13:28,041 --> 00:13:30,521
(CLOCK TICKS SOFTLY)

261
00:14:05,521 --> 00:14:07,001
(GASPS)

262
00:14:18,361 --> 00:14:19,481
What are you doing?

263
00:14:19,601 --> 00:14:21,481
Hey!

264
00:14:25,721 --> 00:14:26,641
Tibo!

265
00:14:26,761 --> 00:14:28,441
DOCTOR: What is your name?

266
00:14:28,561 --> 00:14:29,801
Tahira.

267
00:14:29,921 --> 00:14:32,241
Have you seen those creatures
before, Tahira?

268
00:14:32,361 --> 00:14:33,721
Not really.

269
00:14:33,841 --> 00:14:35,281
Who are you?

270
00:14:35,401 --> 00:14:37,081
I've never seen you here
before, Doctor.

271
00:14:37,201 --> 00:14:40,361
Well, my brief
is quite wide-ranging.

272
00:14:41,681 --> 00:14:44,241
No signs of those creatures
outside the bimaristan.

273
00:14:44,361 --> 00:14:46,121
So, deliberately targeting
a hospital

274
00:14:46,241 --> 00:14:47,561
of vulnerable people.

275
00:14:47,681 --> 00:14:49,521
The place is silent.
Where is everyone else?

276
00:14:49,641 --> 00:14:50,801
How many people were here?

277
00:14:50,921 --> 00:14:52,481
Maybe 10 or 12 patients.

278
00:14:52,601 --> 00:14:53,681
I'm really sorry...

279
00:14:54,881 --> 00:14:56,841
...but I think those creatures
must have taken them.

280
00:14:56,961 --> 00:14:57,881
Taken them where?

281
00:14:58,001 --> 00:14:58,961
I've no idea,

282
00:14:59,081 --> 00:15:02,161
and why they left you
behind...

283
00:15:02,281 --> 00:15:03,681
How long have you been here?

284
00:15:03,801 --> 00:15:05,361
If it's not
a personal question,

285
00:15:05,481 --> 00:15:06,681
which it is.

286
00:15:06,801 --> 00:15:08,241
A few weeks.

287
00:15:08,361 --> 00:15:10,841
I've travelled a long way.

288
00:15:10,961 --> 00:15:12,441
Seen a lot of things
I wish I hadn't.

289
00:15:15,281 --> 00:15:17,121
My family were killed
when I was seven.

290
00:15:17,241 --> 00:15:19,641
I ran.
Aleppo was safety for me.

291
00:15:19,761 --> 00:15:21,761
They let me in here
because I wasn't doing well.

292
00:15:21,881 --> 00:15:23,281
I promise to keep you safe.

293
00:15:23,401 --> 00:15:24,801
We will work this out.

294
00:15:24,921 --> 00:15:26,441
- (PHONE RINGS)
- Ah!

295
00:15:26,561 --> 00:15:27,921
Really sorry.

296
00:15:28,041 --> 00:15:30,361
Message device - someone's
trying to get in touch.

297
00:15:30,481 --> 00:15:32,481
Just in 14th-century Syria.

298
00:15:32,601 --> 00:15:34,161
Is it lunchtime tomorrow
already?

299
00:15:34,281 --> 00:15:35,241
I need your help.

300
00:15:35,361 --> 00:15:36,921
- My mate's been taken.
- What?/

301
00:15:37,041 --> 00:15:38,841
- (PHONE CHIMES)
- Wait. Another call.

302
00:15:38,961 --> 00:15:40,481
- Yaz?
- Doctor,

303
00:15:40,601 --> 00:15:41,801
there was a figure in our flat.

304
00:15:41,921 --> 00:15:43,241
- (PHONE BEEPS)
- Oh, hold on.

305
00:15:43,361 --> 00:15:45,001
(SIGHS) Graham?

306
00:15:45,121 --> 00:15:46,121
Hey, Doc,

307
00:15:46,241 --> 00:15:48,161
I keep seeing these images
of planets,

308
00:15:48,281 --> 00:15:49,921
like they're being projected
into my head.

309
00:15:50,041 --> 00:15:52,441
Mm... Hold on.

310
00:15:52,561 --> 00:15:54,521
Call merge.
I'm going to get you all now,

311
00:15:54,641 --> 00:15:56,601
and I'm bringing
my new friend Tahira.

312
00:15:56,721 --> 00:15:59,041
- ALL: Who?
- I'll be there in a sec.

313
00:15:59,161 --> 00:16:00,361
Ah!

314
00:16:04,361 --> 00:16:05,841
They did leave something
behind.

315
00:16:05,961 --> 00:16:07,001
I knew it.

316
00:16:07,121 --> 00:16:08,641
This will tell us something.

317
00:16:08,761 --> 00:16:11,241
Come on.
I'll explain on the way.

318
00:16:11,361 --> 00:16:13,361
And it might
just blow your mind.

319
00:16:19,801 --> 00:16:23,201
Tahira, this is Ryan,
Graham and Ya-z.

320
00:16:23,321 --> 00:16:25,201
Hi.

321
00:16:25,321 --> 00:16:27,481
Tahira is from Aleppo -
in 1380.

322
00:16:27,601 --> 00:16:29,561
I've explained about the TARDIS
and the fact

323
00:16:29,681 --> 00:16:31,481
that you're from 700 years
in the future.

324
00:16:31,601 --> 00:16:33,721
I'm really not ready for today.

325
00:16:33,841 --> 00:16:34,761
(BEEPING)

326
00:16:34,881 --> 00:16:36,321
No, don't tell me that,
cos you're wrong.

327
00:16:36,441 --> 00:16:37,961
- (BEEPING)
- I'm telling you you are.

328
00:16:38,081 --> 00:16:40,681
- Who is she arguing with?
- The TARDIS.

329
00:16:40,801 --> 00:16:42,561
Because it's telling me,
quite defiantly,

330
00:16:42,681 --> 00:16:45,401
that these two strands of fur
do not exist,

331
00:16:45,521 --> 00:16:46,601
when they're right there!

332
00:16:46,721 --> 00:16:49,201
Those creatures that we saw
aren't registered

333
00:16:49,321 --> 00:16:50,641
in its database.

334
00:16:50,761 --> 00:16:53,001
They've never existed,
will never exist.

335
00:16:53,121 --> 00:16:54,401
Except they must.

336
00:16:54,521 --> 00:16:56,641
Cos if they don't exist,
if they can't exist,

337
00:16:56,761 --> 00:16:59,041
where did they come from
and how?

338
00:16:59,161 --> 00:17:01,801
Tell me what happened
to your mate.

339
00:17:01,921 --> 00:17:02,921
Some guy was in his room.

340
00:17:03,041 --> 00:17:04,441
Don't know how he got in there.

341
00:17:04,561 --> 00:17:07,201
It was like his fingers
were detached from his hand...

342
00:17:07,321 --> 00:17:09,401
...connected to Tibo's ear.
It was draining

343
00:17:09,521 --> 00:17:10,521
something from him.

344
00:17:10,641 --> 00:17:11,881
What did he look like?

345
00:17:12,001 --> 00:17:13,881
He was bald and...
tattooed head.

346
00:17:14,001 --> 00:17:16,601
Whoa. Same bloke
that was in the flat.

347
00:17:16,721 --> 00:17:19,601
And you, the psychic incursion
in your head?

348
00:17:19,721 --> 00:17:21,601
Someone trying to communicate
with you?

349
00:17:21,721 --> 00:17:22,921
GRAHAM: Yeah,
but it was a woman.

350
00:17:23,041 --> 00:17:25,161
She was trapped
inside this, um...

351
00:17:25,281 --> 00:17:27,761
I don't know, I couldn't make
head nor tail of it.

352
00:17:27,881 --> 00:17:31,641
Then I saw these,
um, like, planets.

353
00:17:31,761 --> 00:17:32,921
They were burning,

354
00:17:33,041 --> 00:17:34,561
like she was connected
to them somehow.

355
00:17:34,681 --> 00:17:36,681
Someone is targeting us.

356
00:17:36,801 --> 00:17:39,401
Do you have any idea
where those planets might be?

357
00:17:39,521 --> 00:17:41,281
You get me an A-Z
of the universe,

358
00:17:41,401 --> 00:17:44,281
and I'll be able to stick
my finger straight on...

359
00:17:44,401 --> 00:17:45,681
No, I've got no idea.

360
00:17:45,801 --> 00:17:47,201
Right, then, better idea.

361
00:17:47,321 --> 00:17:49,641
TARDIS telepathic circuits.

362
00:17:49,761 --> 00:17:51,921
- Doc...
- Stop fidgeting, will you?

363
00:17:52,041 --> 00:17:53,761
Ugh! Doc...

364
00:17:53,881 --> 00:17:55,961
Ow! I don't like it.
Are you sure it's safe?

365
00:17:56,081 --> 00:17:57,281
You trust me, don't you?

366
00:17:57,401 --> 00:17:58,481
Have I got to answer that?

367
00:17:58,601 --> 00:17:59,761
Oi!

368
00:17:59,881 --> 00:18:01,161
Is it going to hurt?

369
00:18:01,281 --> 00:18:02,921
No. Probably not.

370
00:18:03,041 --> 00:18:04,601
Maybe. Yeah.

371
00:18:04,721 --> 00:18:06,041
- Ready?
- No!

372
00:18:06,161 --> 00:18:07,361
Focus on the image.

373
00:18:12,481 --> 00:18:15,401
GRAHAM: Whoa! Ouch!

374
00:18:15,521 --> 00:18:18,641
Ah! We found something -
we're moving.

375
00:18:21,001 --> 00:18:22,001
DOCTOR: But where?

376
00:18:24,001 --> 00:18:26,161
(TARDIS THRUMS)

377
00:18:36,521 --> 00:18:39,201
Deep space. Distant future.

378
00:18:40,441 --> 00:18:41,761
Is this what you saw?

379
00:18:41,881 --> 00:18:44,441
GRAHAM: No, nothing like this.

380
00:18:46,641 --> 00:18:48,281
Then, why here?

381
00:18:48,401 --> 00:18:49,761
What did
the telepathic circuits

382
00:18:49,881 --> 00:18:51,561
lock on to?

383
00:18:51,681 --> 00:18:53,361
RYAN: If they were hooked
into your mind,

384
00:18:53,481 --> 00:18:54,921
no wonder we're somewhere dark
and weird.

385
00:18:55,041 --> 00:18:56,361
GRAHAM: Oi!

386
00:18:56,481 --> 00:18:59,041
Do you even know where we are?

387
00:18:59,161 --> 00:19:00,921
Half a galaxy
past the Geskon Straits.

388
00:19:01,041 --> 00:19:02,441
Very little out here.

389
00:19:02,561 --> 00:19:04,641
No civilisations left by now.

390
00:19:04,761 --> 00:19:06,401
It doesn't feel like a ship,
though.

391
00:19:06,521 --> 00:19:10,521
We are in geostationary orbit,
and that would be deliberate,

392
00:19:10,641 --> 00:19:12,121
so why here?

393
00:19:12,241 --> 00:19:14,521
Are we underground?
Is that why it's so dark?

394
00:19:15,681 --> 00:19:17,361
The Doctor reckons
we're in a building,

395
00:19:17,481 --> 00:19:18,801
among the stars.

396
00:19:18,921 --> 00:19:20,161
We've come a long way
from home.

397
00:19:20,281 --> 00:19:23,081
That's impossible. Nobody
can travel across the stars.

398
00:19:23,201 --> 00:19:25,481
YAZ: Unless you're the Doctor.

399
00:19:25,601 --> 00:19:27,041
She's basically the definition
of impossible.

400
00:19:27,161 --> 00:19:28,841
(WHOOSHING)

401
00:19:28,961 --> 00:19:31,401
Oh! Control hub?

402
00:19:31,521 --> 00:19:33,801
Operator activated.

403
00:19:33,921 --> 00:19:36,641
GRAHAM: Oh, now you've got
something there, Doc.

404
00:19:36,761 --> 00:19:40,081
- Yeah, but what?
- There, look.

405
00:19:40,201 --> 00:19:42,401
That is exactly what I saw,

406
00:19:42,521 --> 00:19:43,521
those two objects.

407
00:19:43,641 --> 00:19:46,521
DOCTOR: This must be
a monitor platform.

408
00:19:46,641 --> 00:19:49,841
Observing events in this part
of the solar system.

409
00:19:49,961 --> 00:19:51,161
What are they, like planets?

410
00:19:51,281 --> 00:19:53,601
Looks like they're falling
into each other.

411
00:19:53,721 --> 00:19:55,001
DOCTOR: Colliding.

412
00:19:55,121 --> 00:19:56,241
About to destroy each other.

413
00:19:56,361 --> 00:19:58,361
It's an extinction event.

414
00:19:58,481 --> 00:20:00,721
But they're not colliding,
and they should be.

415
00:20:00,841 --> 00:20:03,241
What's stopping
the final collapse?

416
00:20:04,281 --> 00:20:06,881
Best take a little zoom in.

417
00:20:08,281 --> 00:20:10,361
Whoa! There's something there,

418
00:20:10,481 --> 00:20:14,121
- between those planets.
- RYAN: What sort of something?

419
00:20:14,241 --> 00:20:15,961
DOCTOR: Good question.

420
00:20:16,081 --> 00:20:17,361
Whoa!

421
00:20:17,481 --> 00:20:21,001
The engineering required
to create that

422
00:20:21,121 --> 00:20:23,441
and keep it in place - bravo.

423
00:20:23,561 --> 00:20:26,361
Whoever built that -
round of applause from me.

424
00:20:26,481 --> 00:20:29,161
Doc, can...can you magnify,
like zoom in?

425
00:20:29,281 --> 00:20:30,201
DOCTOR: Why?

426
00:20:30,321 --> 00:20:32,121
Well, I think
there's more to see.

427
00:20:34,041 --> 00:20:36,241
DOCTOR: A tiny geo orb
locked in place.

428
00:20:36,361 --> 00:20:38,081
RYAN: Is there someone
in there?

429
00:20:40,281 --> 00:20:41,681
WOMAN: Are you here?

430
00:20:41,801 --> 00:20:43,481
Is it you?

431
00:20:43,601 --> 00:20:45,041
Th-That's it!

432
00:20:46,081 --> 00:20:48,121
She's trapped.
That's... That's what I saw.

433
00:20:48,241 --> 00:20:49,641
Doc,

434
00:20:49,761 --> 00:20:52,121
- we...we gotta help her out.
- Please!

435
00:20:53,401 --> 00:20:56,281
Hey! Have you seen this?

436
00:20:56,401 --> 00:20:59,321
This whole section
is covered in fingers.

437
00:21:00,841 --> 00:21:02,961
What?! Covered in fingers?

438
00:21:04,321 --> 00:21:05,481
(GASPS)

439
00:21:05,601 --> 00:21:08,401
(SONIC WHIRS)

440
00:21:08,521 --> 00:21:10,121
And there's a signal
coming from them...

441
00:21:11,201 --> 00:21:12,481
...broadcasting into that orb,

442
00:21:12,601 --> 00:21:15,201
- to that girl.
- WOMAN: I'm trapped.

443
00:21:15,321 --> 00:21:18,441
A psychic signal
fed by all this.

444
00:21:18,561 --> 00:21:19,641
But what is it?

445
00:21:19,761 --> 00:21:20,881
(SONIC WHIRS)

446
00:21:21,001 --> 00:21:22,561
- (MECHANICAL HISSING)
- Ah!

447
00:21:23,841 --> 00:21:27,041
This place has so many secrets
to yield.

448
00:21:27,161 --> 00:21:29,121
(SONIC WHIRS)

449
00:21:29,241 --> 00:21:30,681
RYAN: What do you reckon
you've got there?

450
00:21:30,801 --> 00:21:34,161
This tech is powering
this platform,

451
00:21:34,281 --> 00:21:36,081
powering that orb,

452
00:21:36,201 --> 00:21:39,521
keeping it in place
between those two planets.

453
00:21:40,641 --> 00:21:43,441
And at its heart,
a quantum fluctuation lock,

454
00:21:43,561 --> 00:21:46,681
a sequence
of changing combinations,

455
00:21:46,801 --> 00:21:49,921
hundreds of billions
of combinations

456
00:21:50,041 --> 00:21:51,681
every millisecond...

457
00:21:51,801 --> 00:21:54,161
...which would mean that orb...

458
00:21:54,281 --> 00:21:56,161
...IS a prison,

459
00:21:56,281 --> 00:21:57,681
and she's locked in there,

460
00:21:57,801 --> 00:21:59,881
fed by that signal.

461
00:22:01,681 --> 00:22:03,401
A signal of what, though?

462
00:22:04,721 --> 00:22:06,841
Where is Tahira?

463
00:22:20,481 --> 00:22:22,241
Maryam.

464
00:22:24,481 --> 00:22:27,241
(ROARS)

465
00:22:28,441 --> 00:22:30,401
- (GASPS)
-Do you recognise them?

466
00:22:31,801 --> 00:22:32,961
(GROWLING)

467
00:22:33,081 --> 00:22:34,841
The Chagaskas.

468
00:22:34,961 --> 00:22:37,321
Your worst fears,

469
00:22:37,441 --> 00:22:39,721
my creativity.

470
00:22:39,841 --> 00:22:40,841
RYAN: There she is.

471
00:22:40,961 --> 00:22:42,921
Oi, freak-hands,
get away from her.

472
00:22:44,321 --> 00:22:46,721
Plus, you can release
all of these people right now.

473
00:22:46,841 --> 00:22:48,241
And don't you ever
come sneaking

474
00:22:48,361 --> 00:22:49,641
back into my family's flat.

475
00:22:51,121 --> 00:22:52,361
Oh, that's not good.

476
00:22:56,201 --> 00:22:59,121
(WIND HOWLS)

477
00:23:02,281 --> 00:23:04,521
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

478
00:23:13,441 --> 00:23:14,721
Do it right this time.

479
00:23:16,841 --> 00:23:18,841
I won't be calling anyone.

480
00:23:20,001 --> 00:23:21,041
No point.

481
00:23:22,121 --> 00:23:24,081
You're weak.

482
00:23:24,201 --> 00:23:25,961
You run.

483
00:23:27,801 --> 00:23:29,641
Nobody's coming, Yaz.

484
00:23:41,841 --> 00:23:43,281
You're alone in the dark.

485
00:23:47,361 --> 00:23:49,201
(GASPS) Oh, no.

486
00:23:53,041 --> 00:23:54,561
Sonya!

487
00:24:26,721 --> 00:24:28,161
Tibo?

488
00:24:28,281 --> 00:24:30,041
Where you been, man?

489
00:24:32,001 --> 00:24:34,001
We waited for you.
You said you'd be back.

490
00:24:35,321 --> 00:24:36,721
How long you been waiting?

491
00:24:36,841 --> 00:24:38,761
Our whole lives.

492
00:24:40,601 --> 00:24:42,161
What's with all the fire?

493
00:24:42,281 --> 00:24:44,521
The place is burning.

494
00:24:44,641 --> 00:24:46,001
What place?

495
00:24:46,121 --> 00:24:47,561
Earth.

496
00:24:49,321 --> 00:24:51,481
And you weren't here.

497
00:24:53,201 --> 00:24:54,561
I thought we were mates.

498
00:24:56,001 --> 00:24:57,321
(GROWLS)

499
00:24:59,681 --> 00:25:01,161
(SNARLS)

500
00:25:08,521 --> 00:25:10,121
(SIGHS)

501
00:25:17,641 --> 00:25:19,361
Why am I hooked up to this?

502
00:25:27,081 --> 00:25:28,401
Grace...

503
00:25:28,521 --> 00:25:31,121
I'm sorry to tell you,
Mr O'Brien,

504
00:25:31,241 --> 00:25:33,361
your cancer has returned.

505
00:25:33,481 --> 00:25:35,161
What?

506
00:25:35,281 --> 00:25:36,681
No, no, that can't be right.

507
00:25:36,801 --> 00:25:38,681
I-I've had a check-up.

508
00:25:38,801 --> 00:25:40,521
I, um...

509
00:25:40,641 --> 00:25:42,001
Anyway, you're not my doctor.

510
00:25:42,121 --> 00:25:44,641
This time,
it's very aggressive.

511
00:25:46,401 --> 00:25:47,641
Well, how...

512
00:25:47,761 --> 00:25:49,241
How long have I got?

513
00:25:49,361 --> 00:25:51,201
A couple of hours.

514
00:25:53,801 --> 00:25:58,001
Why didn't you save me?

515
00:25:59,241 --> 00:26:01,121
Uh...

516
00:26:01,241 --> 00:26:02,601
Let me... Let me try again.

517
00:26:06,561 --> 00:26:07,801
Now, for most people,

518
00:26:07,921 --> 00:26:09,801
a quantum flux lock
is unbreakable.

519
00:26:09,921 --> 00:26:14,401
100 billion combinations
every millisecond.

520
00:26:14,521 --> 00:26:15,681
But I've got an app for that.

521
00:26:15,801 --> 00:26:19,681
One sonic...connected
to the calculating power

522
00:26:19,801 --> 00:26:20,961
of one TARDIS.

523
00:26:21,081 --> 00:26:22,961
Shouldn't take too long.

524
00:26:24,721 --> 00:26:26,081
And I'm talking myself again,

525
00:26:26,201 --> 00:26:28,121
which means
the others aren't here.

526
00:26:29,401 --> 00:26:30,481
Hello, Doctor.

527
00:26:35,041 --> 00:26:40,161
I've watched you
stumbling round this universe.

528
00:26:41,921 --> 00:26:43,761
I presume
this is all your doing.

529
00:26:45,521 --> 00:26:49,041
Who's that girl in the orb?
And where are my friends?

530
00:26:49,161 --> 00:26:50,881
Who are you?

531
00:26:52,081 --> 00:26:54,161
I go by many names.

532
00:26:54,281 --> 00:26:56,841
My preferred,

533
00:26:56,961 --> 00:26:59,041
my original,

534
00:26:59,161 --> 00:27:01,321
is Zellin.

535
00:27:01,441 --> 00:27:03,681
No.

536
00:27:06,641 --> 00:27:10,081
Zellin's a mythical name,
way beyond this universe.

537
00:27:10,201 --> 00:27:12,721
Zellin was thought to be a god.

538
00:27:12,841 --> 00:27:14,121
I blush.

539
00:27:16,281 --> 00:27:17,761
You can't be.

540
00:27:17,881 --> 00:27:21,721
We immortals need our games,
Doctor.

541
00:27:21,841 --> 00:27:23,561
Eternity is long,

542
00:27:23,681 --> 00:27:26,281
and we are cursed
to see it all.

543
00:27:27,841 --> 00:27:30,681
The Eternals have their games.

544
00:27:30,801 --> 00:27:33,761
The Guardians have
their power struggles.

545
00:27:33,881 --> 00:27:37,521
For me, this dimension

546
00:27:37,641 --> 00:27:41,081
is a beautiful board
for a game.

547
00:27:41,201 --> 00:27:42,961
The toy maker would approve.

548
00:27:43,081 --> 00:27:45,361
And I do like this form -

549
00:27:45,481 --> 00:27:48,401
it's so...small.

550
00:27:48,521 --> 00:27:54,001
To exist within molecules
and atoms is fascinating.

551
00:27:54,121 --> 00:27:56,121
I can shape them,

552
00:27:56,241 --> 00:27:58,201
regrow,

553
00:27:58,321 --> 00:28:01,521
mould my form...

554
00:28:01,641 --> 00:28:04,841
...to provoke fear
from humans...

555
00:28:04,961 --> 00:28:09,361
...as I extract nightmares
from the scared and vulnerable.

556
00:28:10,441 --> 00:28:14,721
- Now, that is a good game.
- Wait.

557
00:28:17,121 --> 00:28:19,241
Are you transmitting
nightmares?

558
00:28:19,361 --> 00:28:20,761
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

559
00:28:20,881 --> 00:28:22,401
Taking nightmares from humans

560
00:28:22,521 --> 00:28:24,001
and forcing them
into the mind of a girl

561
00:28:24,121 --> 00:28:25,761
you've trapped between planets?

562
00:28:26,841 --> 00:28:29,121
I've seen many races, Doctor,

563
00:28:29,241 --> 00:28:32,921
and the humans
are infinitely fascinating,

564
00:28:33,041 --> 00:28:34,921
infinitely...

565
00:28:35,041 --> 00:28:36,321
...pathetic.

566
00:28:36,441 --> 00:28:39,281
But of course you know that.

567
00:28:39,401 --> 00:28:42,441
We share the same obsession.

568
00:28:42,561 --> 00:28:44,361
We are not the same.

569
00:28:44,481 --> 00:28:45,521
No.

570
00:28:46,881 --> 00:28:49,641
You are so much...lesser.

571
00:28:51,561 --> 00:28:53,201
You know the best part
of humanity?

572
00:28:54,321 --> 00:28:57,201
The thing
that truly sets them apart?

573
00:28:58,801 --> 00:29:04,001
The cruelty of their own minds
directed towards themselves.

574
00:29:05,121 --> 00:29:07,561
The doubt. The fear.

575
00:29:09,281 --> 00:29:12,361
The endless voices
telling themselves

576
00:29:12,481 --> 00:29:14,881
that they're incapable
and unworthy.

577
00:29:15,001 --> 00:29:16,241
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

578
00:29:18,161 --> 00:29:20,281
Such an exquisite animal.

579
00:29:21,641 --> 00:29:24,041
Built-in pain.

580
00:29:24,161 --> 00:29:28,361
And the repositories
of that pain - the nightmares.

581
00:29:28,481 --> 00:29:30,441
(THRUMMING)

582
00:29:30,561 --> 00:29:31,561
(BEEPING)

583
00:29:31,681 --> 00:29:35,681
I presume that's your doing,
Doctor. Always interfering.

584
00:29:35,801 --> 00:29:38,041
I've watched you
blunder into this.

585
00:29:38,161 --> 00:29:40,561
"Blundering” - top of my CV,

586
00:29:40,681 --> 00:29:42,121
alongside
"plays well with others”

587
00:29:42,241 --> 00:29:44,401
and "excellent tap dancer
in a crisis".

588
00:29:44,521 --> 00:29:46,081
Almost clever!

589
00:29:47,201 --> 00:29:49,761
But not quite clever enough.

590
00:29:49,881 --> 00:29:51,761
DOCTOR: You're sure about that?

591
00:29:51,881 --> 00:29:54,921
Cos, look, your prisoner,
she's free.

592
00:29:55,041 --> 00:29:59,121
I used your own technology
against you.

593
00:29:59,241 --> 00:30:01,161
No, Doctor.

594
00:30:02,241 --> 00:30:05,681
I used your instincts
against you.

595
00:30:05,801 --> 00:30:06,801
What?

596
00:30:09,001 --> 00:30:11,481
I made the Chagaskas,
targeted the humans...

597
00:30:11,601 --> 00:30:14,041
...to entice you here.

598
00:30:14,161 --> 00:30:16,441
I needed someone
from this realm

599
00:30:16,561 --> 00:30:18,481
to break a lock
from this realm.

600
00:30:18,601 --> 00:30:20,001
Only one would do.

601
00:30:21,121 --> 00:30:22,441
You.

602
00:30:24,361 --> 00:30:25,361
No!

603
00:30:27,641 --> 00:30:30,041
ZELLIN: You did find
the right answer.

604
00:30:30,161 --> 00:30:32,921
You weren't asking
the right questions.

605
00:30:35,241 --> 00:30:37,241
My freedom!

606
00:30:39,521 --> 00:30:42,681
ZELLIN: This platform
isn't my technology.

607
00:30:42,801 --> 00:30:44,561
I didn't make this prison.

608
00:30:44,681 --> 00:30:47,721
She was always
the more powerful of us,

609
00:30:47,841 --> 00:30:49,281
the more dangerous.

610
00:30:49,401 --> 00:30:51,841
That's why they imprisoned her.

611
00:30:53,361 --> 00:30:54,961
I just...

612
00:30:55,081 --> 00:30:58,241
...ride in her slipstream.

613
00:31:04,361 --> 00:31:08,001
Release. After all this time.

614
00:31:10,321 --> 00:31:11,521
I don't understand.

615
00:31:12,601 --> 00:31:13,761
Let me make you.

616
00:31:17,361 --> 00:31:19,081
WOMAN: Two creatures
from another realm

617
00:31:19,201 --> 00:31:21,201
descended into a universe

618
00:31:21,321 --> 00:31:23,841
where they were worshipped
as gods.

619
00:31:23,961 --> 00:31:27,841
They saw two planets
and laid a wager.

620
00:31:27,961 --> 00:31:31,121
Which of them could bring
a planet to destruction first?

621
00:31:31,241 --> 00:31:33,281
The gods set to their game,

622
00:31:33,401 --> 00:31:36,161
sowing chaos
through the populations.

623
00:31:36,281 --> 00:31:37,201
Wars began -

624
00:31:37,321 --> 00:31:39,481
between species,

625
00:31:39,601 --> 00:31:41,481
then between the planets
themselves.

626
00:31:42,721 --> 00:31:45,041
The gods delighted
in the carnage.

627
00:31:45,161 --> 00:31:47,121
It passed the time.

628
00:31:47,241 --> 00:31:48,441
But slowly,

629
00:31:48,561 --> 00:31:51,161
the inhabitants of the worlds
grew wise,

630
00:31:51,281 --> 00:31:54,241
realised what these creatures
had done to them.

631
00:31:54,361 --> 00:31:58,001
They unified and fought back
against their so-called gods.

632
00:31:58,121 --> 00:32:01,601
They set their own planets
into a collision course,

633
00:32:01,721 --> 00:32:03,641
and at the heart
of the collision

634
00:32:03,761 --> 00:32:05,321
they laid a prison.

635
00:32:05,441 --> 00:32:08,641
They trapped one creature
between the planets

636
00:32:08,761 --> 00:32:09,841
for eternity.

637
00:32:10,881 --> 00:32:11,961
The other fled,

638
00:32:12,081 --> 00:32:15,681
vowing to return
to release his eternal partner.

639
00:32:17,161 --> 00:32:18,321
ZELLIN: Wake up, Doctor.

640
00:32:19,401 --> 00:32:21,241
Welcome back.

641
00:32:21,361 --> 00:32:23,841
I hope you understand now.

642
00:32:25,121 --> 00:32:27,601
I wasn't torturing her
with nightmares.

643
00:32:28,841 --> 00:32:31,801
I was feeding her
what she needed to stay sane.

644
00:32:33,081 --> 00:32:35,201
The pain of others.

645
00:32:36,321 --> 00:32:39,201
But even gods need
a helping hand, Doctor.

646
00:32:40,281 --> 00:32:41,281
Thank you.

647
00:32:42,481 --> 00:32:46,841
You won't feel a thing
when this all burns.

648
00:32:48,241 --> 00:32:49,481
Yes, they will.

649
00:32:49,601 --> 00:32:51,361
(CHUCKLES)

650
00:32:53,441 --> 00:32:54,921
Where now?

651
00:32:56,481 --> 00:32:57,881
All those nightmares...

652
00:32:59,561 --> 00:33:00,801
I loved them.

653
00:33:00,921 --> 00:33:02,041
Humans?

654
00:33:03,081 --> 00:33:04,361
Earth.

655
00:33:05,481 --> 00:33:06,681
Let's take them all.

656
00:33:06,801 --> 00:33:08,681
ZELLIN: Yes!

657
00:33:14,361 --> 00:33:15,601
Oh, come on!

658
00:33:51,601 --> 00:33:55,521
What do you think it feels like
for them to be such...

659
00:33:56,601 --> 00:34:00,081
...tiny, ephemeral flashes
of existence?

660
00:34:00,201 --> 00:34:01,441
Hmm!

661
00:34:06,281 --> 00:34:08,481
They feel so much.

662
00:34:09,961 --> 00:34:11,081
It must burn them.

663
00:34:12,321 --> 00:34:13,361
I think it does.

664
00:34:22,401 --> 00:34:24,881
THE MASTER: It's buried deep
in all our memories.

665
00:34:25,001 --> 00:34:27,361
In our identity.

666
00:34:27,481 --> 00:34:30,881
Built on the lie
of the timeless child.

667
00:34:33,321 --> 00:34:35,241
(CLOCK TICKS)

668
00:34:37,721 --> 00:34:39,281
DOCTOR: Hmm.

669
00:34:39,401 --> 00:34:41,281
Right. Think this will hold me,
do you?

670
00:34:49,321 --> 00:34:50,961
(SONIC WHIRS)

671
00:34:51,081 --> 00:34:52,281
- (BEEPING)
- Oh!

672
00:34:52,401 --> 00:34:55,081
Argh! Disgusting.

673
00:34:56,681 --> 00:34:57,481
Agh!

674
00:35:04,761 --> 00:35:07,481
I have just had
the maddest dream.

675
00:35:07,601 --> 00:35:08,561
I know. You all have.

676
00:35:08,681 --> 00:35:10,641
Tranquillising
psycho-extraction.

677
00:35:10,761 --> 00:35:11,961
- I need to get Tibo.
- We have to get

678
00:35:12,081 --> 00:35:14,241
everybody safe and back
to their rightful place.

679
00:35:14,361 --> 00:35:15,481
Well, maybe if you stopped

680
00:35:15,601 --> 00:35:17,241
messing around
with those finger things...

681
00:35:17,361 --> 00:35:19,481
Tapped into
the bio-organic code.

682
00:35:19,601 --> 00:35:20,881
Sonic does fingers!

683
00:35:25,201 --> 00:35:26,601
Down.

684
00:35:30,441 --> 00:35:32,281
Stay.

685
00:35:32,401 --> 00:35:33,721
Good dog.

686
00:35:33,841 --> 00:35:35,081
- Ew!
- DOCTOR: Could be useful.

687
00:35:35,201 --> 00:35:36,681
TIBO: Ryan...

688
00:35:36,801 --> 00:35:38,441
Where am I?

689
00:35:38,561 --> 00:35:40,201
All right, mate.
Try not to freak out, yeah?

690
00:35:40,321 --> 00:35:42,441
But you're on
a floating space platform

691
00:35:42,561 --> 00:35:44,761
in a gravitational pull
between two colliding planets

692
00:35:44,881 --> 00:35:46,001
halfway across the universe

693
00:35:46,121 --> 00:35:48,081
cos of the guy who was stealing
your nightmares

694
00:35:48,201 --> 00:35:49,801
through creepy
detachable fingers.

695
00:35:51,201 --> 00:35:52,321
Prank?

696
00:35:52,441 --> 00:35:54,521
No.

697
00:35:54,641 --> 00:35:56,641
Take me through that again.

698
00:35:56,761 --> 00:35:58,441
- (ROARS)
- (GASPS)

699
00:35:58,561 --> 00:36:00,121
RYAN: What are they?

700
00:36:00,241 --> 00:36:02,881
I know why
they didn't attack you.

701
00:36:03,001 --> 00:36:04,281
Because they're yours.

702
00:36:04,401 --> 00:36:05,841
Zellin, that man,

703
00:36:05,961 --> 00:36:09,081
created the Chagaska
from your nightmares.

704
00:36:09,201 --> 00:36:10,801
They wouldn't kill you,
they couldn't -

705
00:36:10,921 --> 00:36:12,721
because you created them.

706
00:36:14,361 --> 00:36:19,081
So, how do you defeat
two rampaging immortals?

707
00:36:19,201 --> 00:36:21,561
Answer - you don't.

708
00:36:21,681 --> 00:36:24,161
Those two planets...
They've spent a millennia

709
00:36:24,281 --> 00:36:25,841
trying to work out
how to do it.

710
00:36:25,961 --> 00:36:27,321
Well, I think
the motivational speech

711
00:36:27,441 --> 00:36:29,001
needs a bit of work, Doc,
if you don't mi...

712
00:36:29,121 --> 00:36:30,361
And also a plan, by the way.

713
00:36:30,481 --> 00:36:33,641
I've got plans crashing
through my brain all the time.

714
00:36:33,761 --> 00:36:35,001
You want a plan? Come to me.

715
00:36:35,121 --> 00:36:36,761
Identifying which plan
is going to work,

716
00:36:36,881 --> 00:36:38,561
that's the tricky bit.

717
00:36:40,801 --> 00:36:41,801
(GASPS)

718
00:36:48,481 --> 00:36:50,041
This is perfect, Zellin.

719
00:36:51,121 --> 00:36:52,041
You've done well.

720
00:36:52,161 --> 00:36:53,681
Take them all.

721
00:36:53,801 --> 00:36:55,321
Hmm!

722
00:36:55,441 --> 00:36:57,601
Billions in one go.

723
00:36:59,121 --> 00:37:01,441
Gorge on their fears.

724
00:37:01,561 --> 00:37:02,761
Why would we rush?

725
00:37:04,201 --> 00:37:05,681
We have so much time...

726
00:37:07,721 --> 00:37:09,921
...to walk in their nightmares.

727
00:37:13,041 --> 00:37:15,081
We can pass eternity here...

728
00:37:16,441 --> 00:37:17,561
...if we take it slow.

729
00:37:18,961 --> 00:37:20,801
Of course.

730
00:37:27,921 --> 00:37:31,161
I've told you,
there are no bogeymen,

731
00:37:31,281 --> 00:37:34,041
nothing to be worried about.

732
00:37:34,161 --> 00:37:35,281
Night-night.

733
00:37:37,241 --> 00:37:38,601
(BREATHES RAGGEDLY)

734
00:37:38,721 --> 00:37:39,721
(DOOR CLOSES)

735
00:37:48,561 --> 00:37:50,961
(WHOOSHING)

736
00:37:52,321 --> 00:37:54,001
(GASPS)

737
00:37:55,121 --> 00:37:57,921
That's not true.

738
00:38:06,721 --> 00:38:09,361
(SCREAMING)

739
00:38:15,121 --> 00:38:18,521
(GROWLING)

740
00:38:18,641 --> 00:38:19,881
What was that?

741
00:38:20,001 --> 00:38:23,881
I manifested a creature
from a human nightmare.

742
00:38:24,001 --> 00:38:25,881
It's calling across
the time waves.

743
00:38:26,001 --> 00:38:27,001
A pet?

744
00:38:30,801 --> 00:38:33,241
I want to see.

745
00:38:42,081 --> 00:38:45,001
DOCTOR: Oh, nice entrance.

746
00:38:45,121 --> 00:38:48,201
Welcome to Aleppo.
Very beautiful city.

747
00:38:48,321 --> 00:38:50,361
How are you here?

748
00:38:50,481 --> 00:38:53,321
I'm that little bit smarter
than you thought I was.

749
00:38:53,441 --> 00:38:56,841
Now, listen to me -
Earth is not your plaything.

750
00:38:59,161 --> 00:39:01,081
You're wrong about humans.

751
00:39:01,201 --> 00:39:04,361
They're not pathetic.
They're magnificent.

752
00:39:04,481 --> 00:39:07,841
They live with their fears,
doubts, guilts.

753
00:39:07,961 --> 00:39:11,561
They face them down every day,
and they prevail.

754
00:39:12,761 --> 00:39:15,121
That's not weakness.
That's strength.

755
00:39:16,281 --> 00:39:18,041
That's what humanity is.

756
00:39:18,161 --> 00:39:20,201
- Isn't that right, Tahira?
- Yes, Doctor.

757
00:39:20,321 --> 00:39:22,081
Why don't you show them

758
00:39:22,201 --> 00:39:23,721
- how strong you are?
- (GROWLS)

759
00:39:23,841 --> 00:39:24,841
TAHIRA: My Chagaska!

760
00:39:27,161 --> 00:39:28,361
ZELLIN: How can you control it?

761
00:39:28,481 --> 00:39:29,881
(GROWLS)

762
00:39:31,081 --> 00:39:33,801
Literally conquered her fear.

763
00:39:33,921 --> 00:39:36,761
Are you...confronting us?

764
00:39:38,281 --> 00:39:39,361
Yeah!

765
00:39:39,481 --> 00:39:41,561
You immortals -

766
00:39:41,681 --> 00:39:43,801
so entitled, so spoiled.

767
00:39:43,921 --> 00:39:45,081
You never clear up
after yourself.

768
00:39:45,201 --> 00:39:46,201
And you should be
really careful

769
00:39:46,321 --> 00:39:47,481
what you leave lying around.

770
00:39:48,521 --> 00:39:49,961
(RUMBLING)

771
00:39:50,081 --> 00:39:51,961
Sorry. I won't do that again.

772
00:39:52,081 --> 00:39:53,881
Just returning
your lost property.

773
00:39:54,001 --> 00:39:55,201
(SONIC WHIRS)

774
00:39:57,121 --> 00:39:58,801
Thanks for lending
a helping hand.

775
00:39:58,921 --> 00:40:00,881
- Really?
- I couldn't resist.

776
00:40:01,001 --> 00:40:03,401
What's your worst nightmare?

777
00:40:04,721 --> 00:40:06,521
- (WHOOSHING)
- Now, Tahira!

778
00:40:06,641 --> 00:40:08,601
(GROWLS)

779
00:40:10,481 --> 00:40:13,241
- (ROARS)
- (BOTH SCREAM)

780
00:40:13,361 --> 00:40:15,681
TAHIRA: You made
my nightmares real.

781
00:40:15,801 --> 00:40:18,321
Now you can live with them
for all eternity.

782
00:40:18,441 --> 00:40:21,281
Yes! Gods back in their box.

783
00:40:21,401 --> 00:40:22,961
We need to get this
back to the monitor platform...

784
00:40:23,081 --> 00:40:25,601
...and all those people out of
the TARDIS Jacuzzi. Come on!

785
00:40:32,961 --> 00:40:36,121
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)

786
00:40:36,241 --> 00:40:38,721
Slept like a baby last night!

787
00:40:41,521 --> 00:40:42,561
Good, cos you need

788
00:40:42,681 --> 00:40:44,001
all the beauty sleep
you can get.

789
00:40:44,121 --> 00:40:45,961
Oi! Man's still looking fresh.

790
00:40:46,081 --> 00:40:47,281
Oh!

791
00:40:49,801 --> 00:40:51,761
What, you'll be going again?

792
00:40:53,161 --> 00:40:54,201
Yeah.

793
00:40:54,321 --> 00:40:57,121
But you could've told me
the truth about it all.

794
00:40:57,241 --> 00:40:58,641
Would you have believed me?

795
00:40:58,761 --> 00:41:00,001
(INHALES SHARPLY) Nope.

796
00:41:00,121 --> 00:41:01,241
(CHUCKLES)

797
00:41:01,361 --> 00:41:03,441
There's a bit more than
just the world you're seeing.

798
00:41:06,401 --> 00:41:07,641
Do you know
when you'll be back?

799
00:41:07,761 --> 00:41:09,761
Not sure.

800
00:41:11,321 --> 00:41:13,801
Well, don't make it too long.

801
00:41:16,801 --> 00:41:18,801
I need my best mate.

802
00:41:21,281 --> 00:41:24,561
(CHUCKLES) I get a bit lost
without him.

803
00:41:26,481 --> 00:41:27,881
Yeah, I get that too.

804
00:41:31,081 --> 00:41:34,521
Look, I've been looking
at something that might help,

805
00:41:34,641 --> 00:41:35,961
for my mate,

806
00:41:36,081 --> 00:41:38,241
and there's something
I need you to do for me -

807
00:41:38,361 --> 00:41:39,921
and you can't argue.

808
00:41:42,161 --> 00:41:43,681
TIBO: I get down.

809
00:41:43,801 --> 00:41:46,001
And I shut myself off.

810
00:41:47,881 --> 00:41:49,481
And it's like
I'm paralysed with it.

811
00:41:50,561 --> 00:41:53,841
For days, weeks...

812
00:41:54,841 --> 00:41:56,161
It's in control of me.

813
00:41:59,081 --> 00:42:01,681
And I thought I'd try
and do something about it.

814
00:42:01,801 --> 00:42:02,841
I went to the supermarket

815
00:42:02,961 --> 00:42:04,481
just so I could talk
to the cashier,

816
00:42:04,601 --> 00:42:07,081
you know,
get back to human contact.

817
00:42:07,201 --> 00:42:09,361
But I got there...

818
00:42:09,481 --> 00:42:11,841
...and it's
those self-service checkouts!

819
00:42:11,961 --> 00:42:15,121
(GENTLE LAUGHTER)

820
00:42:15,241 --> 00:42:17,441
I haven't said that
to anyone before.

821
00:42:19,161 --> 00:42:20,961
I felt like it was just me.

822
00:42:21,081 --> 00:42:22,681
It's not just you.

823
00:42:38,441 --> 00:42:39,601
(SIGHS)

824
00:42:49,481 --> 00:42:50,801
POLICE OFFICER: Hitchhiking?

825
00:42:52,001 --> 00:42:53,121
No.

826
00:42:53,241 --> 00:42:55,241
Just taking in the view?

827
00:42:55,361 --> 00:42:57,321
Not breaking the law, am I?

828
00:42:57,441 --> 00:42:59,041
OFFICER: No.

829
00:42:59,161 --> 00:43:00,961
Where are you off to?

830
00:43:02,801 --> 00:43:04,201
Away.

831
00:43:04,321 --> 00:43:05,841
It's good there.

832
00:43:05,961 --> 00:43:08,081
- Leave me alone.
- Can't do that.

833
00:43:08,201 --> 00:43:09,521
Why not?

834
00:43:09,641 --> 00:43:11,161
People are worried about you.

835
00:43:11,281 --> 00:43:12,241
No, they're not.

836
00:43:12,361 --> 00:43:14,361
Your sister is.

837
00:43:14,481 --> 00:43:16,801
That's why she called us.

838
00:43:16,921 --> 00:43:18,921
She's worried you've left

839
00:43:19,041 --> 00:43:20,921
and are going to do
something stupid.

840
00:43:23,641 --> 00:43:25,481
I've heard things are tough.

841
00:43:25,601 --> 00:43:27,761
Getting bullied at school.

842
00:43:27,881 --> 00:43:29,401
Grades have gone a bit wonky.

843
00:43:31,081 --> 00:43:32,801
Parents don't get what's up.

844
00:43:36,641 --> 00:43:38,921
You must be feeling
pretty trapped and alone.

845
00:43:40,601 --> 00:43:42,281
I'm feeling way more than that.

846
00:43:43,361 --> 00:43:45,041
(SIGHS)

847
00:43:45,161 --> 00:43:47,241
That's better
than the other way.

848
00:43:47,361 --> 00:43:48,281
What?

849
00:43:48,401 --> 00:43:50,881
Well, feeling things
isn't wrong.

850
00:43:51,001 --> 00:43:53,721
- I don't want your speech.
- I know.

851
00:43:55,281 --> 00:43:58,001
Terrible thing
about being older

852
00:43:58,121 --> 00:44:00,641
is you have all this experience

853
00:44:00,761 --> 00:44:03,481
and nobody
ever wants to hear it.

854
00:44:05,641 --> 00:44:08,801
Cos I know that
there's so much ahead of you.

855
00:44:11,881 --> 00:44:14,881
What if this moment,

856
00:44:15,001 --> 00:44:17,361
where you want to run,
away from everyone,

857
00:44:17,481 --> 00:44:19,001
including yourself,
is just that?

858
00:44:20,401 --> 00:44:21,601
A moment.

859
00:44:22,641 --> 00:44:24,961
What if we find a way
to get you through it

860
00:44:25,081 --> 00:44:26,801
and out of the other side?

861
00:44:32,641 --> 00:44:35,201
I've been where you are.

862
00:44:37,001 --> 00:44:39,041
Moments change.

863
00:44:41,081 --> 00:44:42,401
Help's out there.

864
00:44:42,521 --> 00:44:44,121
As much or as little
as you need.

865
00:44:44,241 --> 00:44:45,681
I'm not listening to you.

866
00:44:48,201 --> 00:44:50,441
Would hard cash
make a difference?

867
00:44:52,161 --> 00:44:54,001
I'll make you a deal.

868
00:44:54,121 --> 00:44:55,521
Look me up in three years.

869
00:44:55,641 --> 00:44:57,401
If I'm wrong,
I'll give you 50 quid.

870
00:44:57,521 --> 00:44:59,641
I mean, I'd say more,
but the pay's rubbish.

871
00:44:59,761 --> 00:45:00,841
Get another job, then.

872
00:45:00,961 --> 00:45:02,961
Can't. Love it too much.

873
00:45:06,081 --> 00:45:07,121
But if I'm right...

874
00:45:08,321 --> 00:45:09,801
...you owe me 50p.

875
00:45:11,801 --> 00:45:14,841
Come on, those are good odds.

876
00:45:35,441 --> 00:45:36,601
(DOOR OPENS)

877
00:45:36,721 --> 00:45:38,921
Hi. Can I help you?

878
00:45:40,161 --> 00:45:42,601
Hi. You won't remember me.
My name's Yasmin.

879
00:45:42,721 --> 00:45:44,081
Yasmin Khan.

880
00:45:44,201 --> 00:45:46,081
I flippin' do remember you.

881
00:45:51,121 --> 00:45:53,161
I've got something for you.

882
00:46:02,001 --> 00:46:03,201
You wanna come in?

883
00:46:06,281 --> 00:46:08,041
GRAHAM: The thing is, Doc,
I worry

884
00:46:08,161 --> 00:46:10,561
about getting sick again.

885
00:46:10,681 --> 00:46:12,281
You know, about the...

886
00:46:12,401 --> 00:46:14,001
...about the cancer
coming back.

887
00:46:14,121 --> 00:46:16,201
And I didn't know
who to say it to,

888
00:46:16,321 --> 00:46:17,761
so I thought I'd say it to you.

889
00:46:19,081 --> 00:46:20,881
You know,
seeing as you're a doctor.

890
00:46:21,001 --> 00:46:23,441
You know, cos once...

891
00:46:23,561 --> 00:46:26,081
...once you have it,
it's with you the whole time.

892
00:46:26,201 --> 00:46:28,201
Not quite a shadow, but...

893
00:46:28,321 --> 00:46:30,601
Hey, don't get me wrong.
I mean, my check-ups,

894
00:46:30,721 --> 00:46:35,081
they're all fine, but it...it
made me think, you know,

895
00:46:35,201 --> 00:46:38,481
and, um, I thought
I should talk about it,

896
00:46:38,601 --> 00:46:41,561
cos those nightmares, I mean...

897
00:46:42,801 --> 00:46:44,321
(CLEARS THROAT)
Well, they made me realise

898
00:46:44,441 --> 00:46:48,041
that the fear is...is...is
still there, you know.

899
00:46:49,601 --> 00:46:51,601
(THRUMMING)

900
00:46:54,921 --> 00:46:57,121
I should say a reassuring thing
now, shouldn't I?

901
00:46:58,681 --> 00:47:00,441
Yeah, probably.

902
00:47:00,561 --> 00:47:02,561
I'm still
quite socially awkward.

903
00:47:02,681 --> 00:47:04,321
(THRUMMING)

904
00:47:04,441 --> 00:47:07,361
So I'm just going to subtly
walk towards the console

905
00:47:07,481 --> 00:47:08,961
and look at something.

906
00:47:09,081 --> 00:47:11,481
And then, in a minute...

907
00:47:12,881 --> 00:47:15,401
...I'll think of something
that I should've said...

908
00:47:17,081 --> 00:47:18,441
...that might
have been helpful.

909
00:47:18,561 --> 00:47:20,921
(LAUGHS) OK.

910
00:47:21,041 --> 00:47:22,681
Well...

911
00:47:22,801 --> 00:47:24,521
(CLEARS THROAT)
I'm glad we had this chat, eh?

912
00:47:24,641 --> 00:47:26,601
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

913
00:47:27,681 --> 00:47:29,681
RYAN: How long
is this going to last, Yaz?

914
00:47:30,801 --> 00:47:31,961
Hanging out with the Doctor?

915
00:47:33,641 --> 00:47:35,241
I don't know.

916
00:47:35,361 --> 00:47:37,041
Is this our lives?

917
00:47:37,161 --> 00:47:40,201
Going from one place
to the next, ignoring home?

918
00:47:40,321 --> 00:47:43,481
We're getting older,
but without them.

919
00:47:45,761 --> 00:47:47,681
Missing out
bits of their lives.

920
00:47:47,801 --> 00:47:49,321
When we're done,
the Doctor can drop you off

921
00:47:49,441 --> 00:47:50,801
at whatever point you want,
though.

922
00:47:50,921 --> 00:47:52,841
Yeah, but we'll have changed.
They wouldn't have.

923
00:47:53,961 --> 00:47:55,801
It's like we're living
at different rates.

924
00:47:55,921 --> 00:47:57,841
The Doctor said we wouldn't
come back the same.

925
00:48:00,121 --> 00:48:02,961
I was thinking...
Frankenstein.

926
00:48:03,081 --> 00:48:04,241
- BOTH: What?
- Did I interrupt?

927
00:48:04,361 --> 00:48:05,321
Am I interrupting?

928
00:48:05,441 --> 00:48:07,321
- No.
- Cool.

929
00:48:07,441 --> 00:48:09,401
You might need
a change of clothes!

930
00:48:11,001 --> 00:48:14,121
- On we go.
- On we go.

931
00:48:14,241 --> 00:48:16,081
Hi.

932
00:48:26,241 --> 00:48:28,081
(TARDIS THRUMS)

933
00:48:58,121 --> 00:49:00,521
How about writing
the most gruesome,

934
00:49:00,641 --> 00:49:03,841
spine-chilling ghost story
of all time?

935
00:49:04,841 --> 00:49:08,121
- (ALL SCREAM)
- Tales Of The Dead.

